f(x)=0.2
0 \le x \le 0.5
2.4x-1
0.5 \le x \le 1
\mu = \int xf(x)dx
\sigma^2=\int x^2f(x)dx-\mu^2
\mu = \int xf(x)dx = \int_0^{\frac12} 0.2x dx + \int_{\frac12}^1 x(2.4x-1)dx
X
\left[0,1\right]
f_{X}
f_{X}\left(x\right)=f_{1}\left(x\right)
x\in\left[0,0.5\right]
f_{X}\left(x\right)=f_{2}\left(x\right)
g\left(x\right)=x
\mathbb{E}X
g\left(x\right)=x^{2}
\mathbb{E}X^{2}
\mathbb{E}g\left(X\right)=\int g\left(x\right)f_{X}\left(x\right)dx=\int_{0}^{0.5}g\left(x\right)f_{1}\left(x\right)dx+\int_{0.5}^{1}g\left(x\right)f_{2}\left(x\right)dx
\text{Var}\left(X\right)=\mathbb{E}X^{2}-\left(\mathbb{E}X\right)^{2}
